    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-16T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="21"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34553B/110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-16T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 16, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>811. For the Secretary and Matthews. I would comment, in connection with the last
                    part of London’s telegram No. 2058 to the Department,<note n="51"
                        xml:id="d21fn1">Not printed.</note> that it is important that the British
                    Ambassador be instructed to state in writing to Salazar not merely that his
                    Government desires that negotiations for a second airfield be conducted directly
                    between the United States and Portugal but also that they reach a speedy and
                    successful termination without recourse to the Anglo-Portuguese agreement of
                    August 17. It should thus be made clear that the British Government fully
                    supports our desire to build and operate on our own behalf the second
                    airfield.</p>
                <p>Reference is also made to your 750, March 11, 7 p.m.<note n="51" xml:id="d21fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
